text: Pomeranian Voivodeship is a voivodeship, or province, in northwestern Poland. The provincial capital is Gdańsk. The voivodeship was made on January 1, 1999, out of the former voivodeships of Gdańsk, Elbląg and Słupsk. There are two national parks in Pomerania: Słowiński National Park and Tuchola Forest National Park. Category:1999 establishments in Poland
title: Pomeranian Voivodeship
